{
  "stem": "23090.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was a young survivor and they thought they were doing something good.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was performing a service, another way of surviving.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's another step in the road to survival.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were great.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So from there I met a Polish lieutenant, Lieutenant Pollack, Pollack from San Francisco.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's a wonderful guy, not a Jew, just a human, wonderful human being.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he took off a week, almost two weeks and went around with me to camps, believe it or not, trying to find relatives and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I tried-- I communicated with him a little bit after that, thanking him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I sent him a-- you know, said-- then I lost touch with him, contact with him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, you know, things were starting to move so fast, and--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I didn't find-- well, what had happened is that we were gathered by this Jewish rabbi and we were asked if we wanted to leave to Israel.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, Israel was not in existence at the time, but [NON-ENGLISH] as we was forming, or come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I chose to come here because I already was somewhat Americanized, the GI's, and I liked that life, and I liked the kindness, and I kind of related to that more, not anything less than the Jewish Israeli tradition.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this is where I wanted to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And from that point, the Jewish Children's Bureau took over.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they sponsored us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this rabbi went to the Eisenhower headquarters, the theater, and asked for special dispensations, special permission, to have us leave without quotas.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is way before quotas and way before, you know, immigration laws and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
